The paper deals with algorithms for analyzing multiple objectives in Markov automata, which are commonly used in reliability engineering, performance evaluation, and stochastic scheduling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the adoption of existing approaches for classical Markov decision processes, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
